author: Russell Brand
description:
A discussion on whether decentralised power truly leads to freedom or simply replaces central authority with endless local conflict, drawing comparisons between tribal warfare, the collapse of empires, and Britain’s ability to absorb dissent. The conversation moves through revolutions past and present, from Napster’s disruption of the music industry to sudden political upheavals across Europe and Latin America, questioning whether rapid systemic collapse and reform are now inevitable.
